social_posts.post_text: People always ask me if I show up the day of the wedding or does my team execute everything. I answer with, “I am the first one in and the last one out.” I have a great team but as a designer/planner I also like to be hands on as many of the things I know that is important to my clients are said verbally and stored in my head and for me it’s important that the client knows I am there for them. Plus I still love the magic of the transformation and seeing what I designed come to life. Yes on the day of the wedding I’m usually on my feet for 17 hours, this does not include load-in days and load-out days which I am on site for as well. It’s worth it but when it’s all over I take a day off with a big DO NOT DISTURB sign, as my body is usually spent and I mentally dump all that occurred. Wedding planning is not for the weak. 📸 @jennyquicksall

social_posts.post_text: Travel truly makes you appreciate humanity and the world. It gives you a different perspective and understanding for culture and people that can’t be learned in books or TV - you truly need to experience it in person to have a true appreciation. I would take a chance to discover the world over any material gifts anytime!

Never take for granted the opportunities given in life. I truly believe things happen and placed before you at the perfect time (good and bad) and they are all opportunities to grow personally. As the new year approaches let’s keep moving one foot at a time, one moment at a time and be grateful for opportunities to becoming the best you.

The first month of 2023 is almost over…how is it going so far? Any surprises? Any wow moments? Any resets? It’s okay to make adjustments to where you need to be this year…just remember that you got this and no matter what comes your way…SLAY!
My new daily routine. Thank you @jeniferlewisforreal for that morning check! #lifehack

Ross and I have been together for 31 years. 3 decades…we’ve been together more than half our lives! We’ve grown so much since our early 20s and have been through so many up’s, downs and everything in between since then. BUT I would choose to do it over and over again with my Ross…it truly is a life of love, laughter and adventure…but mostly sitting around in our underwear drinking wine and eating @benandjerrys 😂 While it hasn’t always been perfect, I can’t think of anyone better to be my ride or die.

social_posts.post_text: Percy Sales events has entered a new era and I am also excited to announce the launch of @curatedbypercy a new fun venture. It’s been 23 years since Percy Sales events became a reality, I’ve grown, the brand has grown, and we look totally different than we did in 2000. Seeing how my brand has changed through the years is surreal at times…the highs and the lows, cheers and tears, I’m amazed at the journey. So…I’m focusing on the name, my name, and thus the rebrand. While the logo may seem simple, there’s so much meaning in it, may not be obvious to you but it’s clearly there for me and will be a daily reminder. I am currently working on a new website that will launch soon…but for now I give you the new logo and brand. Total 360…but I believe this is where I am and where I am heading! I’m looking forward to what the future has in store! Thank you to @branded.media_agency + @woodlandcellar for working with me the last few months to realize this next reiteration of Percy Sales events…I could have not done it without the two of you! And International Wedding Planner Day was the appropriate time to share this! #rebranded #branding #newera #fresh #thisisme

I really love sharing my story and my experiences. I think we learn from each other - from our highs and our lows. Our journeys are all unique we can’t compare it to anyone else. The only thing we can do is to find a tribe that pushes us forward, find support in and outside of your circle. Know when to help and when to ask for help. Appreciate your own journey and accomplishments. Ultimately, learn to know your superpowers and your kryptonite. You can’t please everyone nor get the support from everyone - you’ll always have individuals who pray for your failure…and that’s okay…all you can do is prove them wrong and prove yourself right. When you falter, remember to stand up, brush off the dust, and walk one step at a time with your head held high. Life is a rollercoaster ride…just put your hands up, scream, and enjoy the ride. 📸 @xandercaseyphotography #motivationalspeaker #lifeofaweddingplanner #makingmoves #silencethevoices #believe #live #justfine #survivor

I can finally share the design I did for the @tabledesignexhibition in Istanbul. 

I did a design that was not expected…not the prettiest but it was the happiest. It’s a bit gritty, thoughtful, with elegance…a bit moody but internally joyful. It was a color explosion that was casted with dark undertones and some clouds. A bit basic from first look and then your realize it’s more complex than you thought. It is like me…some will get it, some will think wtf, some will love it and some will hate it…at least it gave you some feels and I guess that is all that matters…it gave you a reaction a lot like street art. But hopefully you dug a little deeper into it to understand it. As with anything discovering the layers is the magic.

I incorporated unexpected items like a wall full of smashed up paints cans (representing people who are not perfect yet has a lot of joy trapped in them) and spray cans on the table, main centerpiece floral spilling out of a dented paint can with it dripping and spilling on the floor. Spray cans as luxury…what? The other centerpieces were meant to be like paint jumping off the tables after spilling from above. It’s where beauty and gritty lives in harmony. Where opposites intertwine to make magic.

It’s titled Head in the Clouds 

My statement: “My table reflects the art seen throughout Turkiye. From street art to antiquities I am inspired by the textures, the colors and the history you see everyday. I’m inspired by the vibrancy of color throughout Turkiye, which feeds my soul and imagination with so many possibilities. Additionally, with so much “eye candy” from every corner of the country - you can’t help finding yourself with your head in the clouds - dreaming, hoping, and creating.” 

The spray can menus read:

Starter:
Nothing happens unless we first dream.
Main Course:
Open your heart and drink in this glorious day.
Sweet Ending:
Gratitude is a celebration we are all invited to.

This year has flown by…20 days until 2024. I can’t believe how much has changed this year and how much I’ve grown. It’s been a year of so many highs and so many challenges. A year of patience, growth and understanding. A year of adventure and connecting. A year of rediscovering who I am as an individual. I’ve even changed physically. I’ve dropped 50lbs since 2022, grew my hair out and feeling this might be a midlife awakening…but whatever it is I’m here for it. 2023 truly was an epic year. I hope 2024 delivers half of what this year offered. I’m definitely not the same person I was when I was a teen and I am much stronger than I was in 2022. Growth and change is inevitable and we should embrace it with grace. It’s reminds me of this quote which I will embrace for the remainder of 2023…“Change and growth take place when a person has risked himself and dares to become involved with experimenting with his own life.”—Herbert Otto. I could have not done this without the support of my husband, he truly encourages me to be me. Let the countdown to 2024 begin! 📸 @marlieshartmann
